info.description:
IMPS APIs use dynamic URLs with txn_id. Same txn_id is used for the full flow (NPCI → IMPS → Switch → IMPS → NPCI).

- NPCI → IMPS: POST http://localhost:8081/imps/{reqpay|reqchktxn|reqvaladd|reqhbt|reqlistaccpvd}/{txn_id}
- IMPS → Switch: POST http://localhost:8082/switch/{reqpay|reqchktxn|reqvaladd|reqhbt|reqlistaccpvd}/{txn_id}
- Switch → IMPS: POST http://localhost:8081/switch/{resppay|respchktxn|respvaladd|resphbt|resplistaccpvd}/{txn_id}
- IMPS → NPCI: POST http://localhost:8083/npci/{resppay|respchktxn|respvaladd|resphbt|resplistaccpvd}/{txn_id}

ACK: IMPS returns <ns2:Ack ... api="ReqPay" reqMsgId="" ts=""></ns2:Ack>. reqMsgId = Head @msgId from request (required). api = message type (ReqPay, RespPay, etc.). Duplicate txn_id returns 409. Missing reqMsgId returns 400.

Message ID (msgId): Exactly 35 characters = Bank Participation Code (3, assigned by NPCI) + Unique ID (32, UUID/random/system-generated). Mandatory for ACK. txnId (Txn @id): same format, 35 chars. Use unique values per request.

Ports: IMPS 8081, Mock Switch 8082, NPCI Mock 8083.
